{
  "stem": "21008.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] From Auschwitz, we received from my uncle an illegal letter, , which I do not have anymore because my father destroyed it out of fear.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had smuggled that letter [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] out of the camp with a-- a German worker who came into the camp to do I don't know what.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he left the camp at night.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And fortunately, that-- that man was good enough to smuggle that letter out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in that letter, my uncle told us that on-- upon arrival, he was separated from his wife and the two girls, and he never saw them again, and that he is put to work-- very hard work in the beginning.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But at that time, when he wrote the letter, he was better off because he was in the orchestra.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was an-- an-- on-- in Auschwitz was an orchestra that had to play every morning and every night.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he was in that orchestra.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But he also died.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He lived until January of '44, which I learned later from somebody who survived Auschwitz and who was together with him, and who had known him from the earlier years.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So we had authentic report of his demise, if you want to call it that way.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He died.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He was not gassed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He died, as far as I know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And your husband-to-be, you mentioned also, was underground at some point in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They went-- the-- the family Winterfeldt-- his mother, his father, and he went underground on February 15, 1943-- lived underground with the help of all different kinds of people until June 12, 1944.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Two days prior to that, my ex-husband had met somebody who he had worked with.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
